in a patrol car.

12:28.530 --> 12:31.925
We collided.
Our vehicles flipped.

12:31.968 --> 12:34.362
I must have
lost consciousness
for a moment

12:34.405 --> 12:37.104
because I don'’t remember
Zeke getting out.

12:38.670 --> 12:41.064
I just seen him standing
next to The Artist and...

12:42.849 --> 12:44.285
And what?

12:48.289 --> 12:51.161
Zeke doused himself
in gasoline

12:51.205 --> 12:53.903
and set himself on fire.

13:07.830 --> 13:09.789
[pendant jingling]

13:30.592 --> 13:33.421
[Dr. Loesch] Mr. Lefeuvre is
monitored around the clock.

13:33.464 --> 13:38.295
He'’s actually the only resident
of a psychiatric institution
scheduled for execution.

13:38.339 --> 13:40.080
The court declared
him sane, right?

13:40.123 --> 13:43.083
Yes, I read
the mental evaluation
presented at his trial.

13:43.126 --> 13:44.214
And you disagree?

13:44.258 --> 13:46.129
My opinion'’s irrelevant.

13:46.173 --> 13:49.654
The Artist was transferred
here to prevent
any further self-harm.

13:50.264 --> 13:51.439
Self-harm?

13:51.482 --> 13:52.875
Slashing his wrists

13:52.919 --> 13:55.835
and painting on the walls
in his own blood.

13:59.795 --> 14:00.840
Thank you.

14:25.212 --> 14:26.691
[chains rattling]

14:46.233 --> 14:51.412
-Mr. Lefeuvre, my name is
Detective Mary Kelly.
-I know who you are.

14:51.455 --> 14:55.677
-Sorry. Did someone tell you
that I was coming?
-Yes. A winged friend told me.

14:57.722 --> 14:59.507
Well, I'’m sure someone like you

14:59.550 --> 15:03.511
